            <title>[ZOOKEEPER-3656] SyncRequestProcessor doesn&apos;t update lastFlushTime correctly on observers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-3656</link>
                <project id="12310801" key="ZOOKEEPER">ZooKeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issues was introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/zookeeper/pull/851&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;ZOOKEEPER-3311&lt;/a&gt;. The lastFlushTime used to decide the batch window is not updated correctly for the observer case when the nextProcessor is always be null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can cause observers to fall behind and their sync queue to grow indefinitely.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
